items.title: Rays win on 2 HRs in home away from home
items.summary: Sonny Gray breezed into the eighth inning, turning in one of his sharpest efforts since being acquired by the Yankees. Adeiny Hechavarria rewrote that story with one swing, lifting the Rays to a 2-1 victory on Tuesday evening at Citi Field.

items.title: O's skid up to 6 thanks to Urena's walk-off hit
items.summary: Richard Urena continued to build his hype with a walk-off single off Orioles closer Zach Britton to give the Blue Jays a 3-2 win.

items.title: Braves knock around Gio, shut out Nationals
items.summary: The Braves helped the Nationals wrap up the National League East on Sunday afternoon, but Atlanta did Washington no favors during an 8-0 thumping Tuesday night at Nationals Park.
